  "text": "The profile of excitability changes presented in Figure 8 is consistent with changes in A-type K ϩ current [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and suggests that AKAP79/150 regulation of Kv4.2 phosphorylation state fundamentally impacts neuronal excitability. To confirm that AKAP PKA anchoring contributes to the intrinsic excitability of hippocampal neurons through regulation of A-type K ϩ currents, we treated neurons with the intracellular K ϩ channel blocker, 4-aminopyridine (4-AP) (5 mM), alone or together with Ht31 or FK506 in the pipette. Results showed that, compared with control, intracellular 4-AP significantly increased neuronal excitability (Fig. 8C-F , Table 1 ; n ϭ 12 for 4-AP; n ϭ 13 for 4-AP ϩ Ht31, n ϭ 12 for 4-AP ϩ FK506; p Ͻ 0.05). However, with 4-AP treatment, neither Ht31 nor FK506 altered neuronal excitability (Fig. 8C-F, Table 1 ; p Ͼ 0.1), demonstrating that AKAP79/150 likely affects excitability through regulation of 4-AP-sensitive Kv4.2 surface expression.",
